## Auto-Invoke Skills - MANDATORY
# Skills fire based on what you are doing - no slash commands needed.
# Remove sections for stacks you do not use.

### Planning and Design

**brainstorming** - invoke when:
- Any new feature, component, or capability ("I want to add X", "build me Y")
- Open-ended decisions: "What should I do about X", "How should I approach this"
- Do NOT invoke for: typo fixes, config tweaks, single-line already-specified changes

**writing-plans** - invoke when:
- Task will touch more than 3 files or take more than 20 minutes
- Complexity is not clear and you need to map it before acting

### UI and Frontend
# Remove this section if you do not do frontend work

**ui-ux-pro-max** - invoke when:
- Any React component, JSX, CSS, Tailwind, or Electron renderer work
- "Make this look better", "redesign", "add a card", "style this"
- Do NOT invoke for: backend logic, scripts, CLI tools, database queries

**design-motion-principles** - invoke when:
- Adding hover states, transitions, animations, micro-interactions
- "Animate this", "this feels sluggish", "add some life to it"
- Do NOT invoke for: static layouts with no motion

### Debugging and Quality

**systematic-debugging** - invoke when:
- Any error, exception, crash, or unexpected output
- "This is not working", "why is X happening", "something broke"
- Do NOT invoke for: planned refactors with no error present

**verification-before-completion** - invoke before EVERY completion claim:
- Run the actual command, see the actual output, then report
- Never say "done" without evidence

### Execution

**executing-plans** - invoke when a plan exists and it is time to run it

**finishing-a-development-branch** - invoke when:
- Implementation is complete, tests pass
- "Wrap this up", "is this ready to ship"

### Codebase Navigation
# REQUIRES: graphify installed (see docs/graphify-setup.md)

graphify query - invoke for ANY codebase question before opening any file:
```
graphify query "question" --graph "[PROJECT_PATH]/graphify-out/graph.json"
```
- "How does auth work?" -> query first
- "Where is the webhook handler?" -> query first
- Never open files to explore code. Query, then open specific files only if query is insufficient.

### Research
# REQUIRES: fabric (https://github.com/danielmiessler/fabric) and markitdown (pip install markitdown)

| Content | Command |
|---------|---------|
| Article or blog URL | `curl -sL URL \| fabric -p summarize` |
| Key insights from URL | `curl -sL URL \| fabric -p extract_wisdom` |
| PDF or Word doc | `markitdown file.pdf` then read the output |
| YouTube video | `yt-dlp --write-auto-sub --skip-download URL` then `markitdown *.vtt \| fabric -p summarize` |

